<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Kampf:
[B]A lot of this applies to me, since, my guild has been attempting to get Ragefire extensively in the last two weeks or so.

In my opinion, if Ragefire is up, he's fair game, and it's the responsibility of the people who spot him to gather the required forces to take him down before other groups do so.  Though I feel this is the case, I know that a lot of the guilds on my server(including my own) would not attempt to 'steal' Ragefire if another guild was mobalizing for him before our own.  For this reason we stick anywhere from 6-12 people in his lair to watch for him.

In the case of the druid tracking for Rage, they have no right to claim Ragefire, even though they have spent how many ever hours sitting there tracking for him.  It takes very little effort to log a druid/ranger alt at the SolA Bugs/Bats zone to just track every 5 minutes while you go off and do other things.  I personally have used this method, having a druid alt, but people who do should realize that other guilds will just shrug it off and take Ragefire anyway.

While actively camping the lair and killing FGs with a number of people, I know that most guilds on my server would have no problem with accepting that Ragefire is being watched for and just go their seperate ways if they believed that the competition too fierce.  If the group in the lair takes too long to mobalize, it's fair game for other guilds who wish to take him, but it's their decission to put their reputation on the line for a silly item.

In short, Rage is FFA, no matter if you have your entire guild sitting in the lair with you, or you are camping it solo with a low level alt.[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
